boeing strike
-
- Updated
As featured on
Machinists at Boeing have voted to go on strike, another setback for the giant aircraft maker whose reputation and finances have been battered and now faces a shutdown in production of its best-selling airline planes. The International Association of Machinists and Aerospace Workers says its members on Thursday rejected a contract that would have raised pay 25% over four years, then voted to strike. A two-thirds vote among 33,000 workers was needed to strike.
